title: Check out this article from our Programs Associate, Cassie Archdeacon, where she explores the complex relationship between AI and human creativity, particularly for young people. While she confesses a deep discomfort with the idea of a non-human touch in art, she challenges herself to look beyond the final product to the creative process, arguing that if generative AI can provide the "spark" to get a young person creating, it's better than making nothing at all.
translated_title: 请查看我们的项目助理 Cassie Archdeacon 撰写的这篇文章，她在其中探讨了人工智能与人类创造力（尤其是年轻人的创造力）之间的复杂关系。虽然她承认对艺术中非人类接触的想法深感不安，但她挑战自己，要超越最终产品，关注创作过程，她认为，如果生成式人工智能能够提供“火花”让年轻人进行创作，那总比什么都不做要好。

title: Check out this article from our COO Dr. Kristine Gloria, where she urges us to Prioritize Youth in AI and Work because it is, fundamentally, their future. She analyzes how recent studies showing a decline in early-career employment due to generative AI create a challenging narrative, even as new job opportunities are simultaneously being speculated, making the future of the labor market a "volatile, uncertain, complex and ambiguous" landscape that young people cannot be expected to navigate alone.
translated_title: 请阅读我们的首席运营官 Kristine Gloria 博士撰写的这篇文章，她在文中敦促我们优先考虑人工智能和工作中的年轻人，因为从根本上来说，这就是他们的未来。她分析了最近的研究显示，由于生成式人工智能导致职业生涯早期就业率下降，尽管人们同时在猜测新的工作机会，但如何创造出一种具有挑战性的叙述，使劳动力市场的未来成为一个“不稳定、不确定、复杂和模糊”的局面，不能指望年轻人独自应对。

title: Check out this article from our Communications Associate, Brooke Messaye, where she argues that for Gen Z, digital literacy is no longer enough; young people now need AI agency—the ability to understand, influence, and even build the AI systems that are rapidly reshaping their futures. She explores how without this agency, Gen Z risks becoming passive consumers whose data fuels algorithms that work against their best interests in the job market, creative economy, and social lives.
translated_title: 请阅读我们的传播助理 Brooke Messaye 撰写的这篇文章，她在文中认为，对于 Z 世代来说，数字素养已经不够了；还需要更多的知识。年轻人现在需要人工智能机构——理解、影响甚至构建正在迅速重塑他们未来的人工智能系统的能力。她探讨了如果没有这个机构，Z 世代将如何面临成为被动消费者的风险，他们的数据推动的算法不利于他们在就业市场、创意经济和社交生活中的最佳利益。
